hpnicfDomain.name: hpnicfDomain
hpnicfDomain.description: The MIB module is used for managing domain.

HpnicfModeOfDomainScheme.name: HpnicfModeOfDomainScheme
HpnicfModeOfDomainScheme.description: The scheme mode of the domain. none: indicates the domain has no scheme. local:indicates the domain will use local-server as a scheme. radius:indicates the domain will use radius scheme. tacacs:indicates the domain will use tacacs scheme. ldap:indicates the domain will use ldap scheme.

HpnicfAAATypeDomainScheme.name: HpnicfAAATypeDomainScheme
HpnicfAAATypeDomainScheme.description: The service type of the server.

HpnicfAccessModeofDomainScheme.name: HpnicfAccessModeofDomainScheme
HpnicfAccessModeofDomainScheme.description: The access mode of the domain.

hpnicfDomainDefault.name: hpnicfDomainDefault
hpnicfDomainDefault.description: Specifies default domain on the equipment. Default value is 'system'.

hpnicfDomainInfoEntry.name: hpnicfDomainInfoEntry
hpnicfDomainInfoEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing a domain.

hpnicfDomainName.name: hpnicfDomainName
hpnicfDomainName.description: An index uniquely identifies a domain.

hpnicfDomainState.name: hpnicfDomainState
hpnicfDomainState.description: The state of the domain, which reflects whether the domain is active. Default value is active.

hpnicfDomainMaxAccessNum.name: hpnicfDomainMaxAccessNum
hpnicfDomainMaxAccessNum.description: The maximum number which the domain allows to access. If the value is set to 0, the access limit will be disabled.

hpnicfDomainVlanAssignMode.name: hpnicfDomainVlanAssignMode
hpnicfDomainVlanAssignMode.description: The vlan assignment mode. The mode SHOULD be the same as the mode of corresponding server. 1 (integer) - Integer Vlan assignment mode. 2 (string) - String Vlan assignment mode. 3 (vlanlist) - VLAN-List Vlan assignment mode. The default value is integer.

hpnicfDomainIdleCutEnable.name: hpnicfDomainIdleCutEnable
hpnicfDomainIdleCutEnable.description: The idle cut control. Setting this attribute to true, the connection will be cut when the flow is less than hpnicfDomainIdleCutMinFlow and lasts hpnicfDomainIdleCutMaxTime. Default value is false.

hpnicfDomainIdleCutMaxTime.name: hpnicfDomainIdleCutMaxTime
hpnicfDomainIdleCutMaxTime.description: The maximal time of idle-cut. The unit is minute. If the value of hpnicfDomainIdleCutEnable is false, the value of hpnicfDomainIdleCutMaxTime is meaningless.

hpnicfDomainIdleCutMinFlow.name: hpnicfDomainIdleCutMinFlow
hpnicfDomainIdleCutMinFlow.description: The minimal flow of idle-cut. The unit is byte. If the value of hpnicfDomainIdleCutEnable is false, the value of hpnicfDomainIdleCutMinFlow is meaningless.

hpnicfDomainMessengerEnable.name: hpnicfDomainMessengerEnable
hpnicfDomainMessengerEnable.description: The messenger service control. If set hpnicfDomainMessengerEnable to true, hpnicfDomainMessengerLimitTime and hpnicfDomainMessengerSpanTime must be set to valid values. Default value is false.

hpnicfDomainMessengerLimitTime.name: hpnicfDomainMessengerLimitTime
hpnicfDomainMessengerLimitTime.description: The messenger service limit time. The unit is minute. If the value of hpnicfDomainMessengerEnable is false, the value of hpnicfDomainMessengerLimitTime is meaningless.

hpnicfDomainMessengerSpanTime.name: hpnicfDomainMessengerSpanTime
hpnicfDomainMessengerSpanTime.description: The messenger service span time. The unit is minute. It must be a multiple of 5. If the value of hpnicfDomainMessengerEnable is false, the value of hpnicfDomainMessengerSpanTime is meaningless.

hpnicfDomainSelfServiceEnable.name: hpnicfDomainSelfServiceEnable
hpnicfDomainSelfServiceEnable.description: The self service control. If set hpnicfDomainSelfServiceEnable to true, hpnicfDomainSelfServiceURL must be set to a valid value. Default value is FALSE.

hpnicfDomainSelfServiceURL.name: hpnicfDomainSelfServiceURL
hpnicfDomainSelfServiceURL.description: Self-service URL(Uniform Resource Locator) of the domain.

hpnicfDomainAccFailureAction.name: hpnicfDomainAccFailureAction
hpnicfDomainAccFailureAction.description: Defines the action that authentication should be taken if authentication succeeds but the associated accounting start fails. 1 (ignore) - treat as authentication success; ignore accounting start failure. 2 (reject) - treat as authentication failed if corresponding accounting start fails. Default value is reject.

hpnicfDomainRowStatus.name: hpnicfDomainRowStatus
hpnicfDomainRowStatus.description: This object is responsible for managing the creation, deletion and modification of rows, which supports active status and CreateAndGo, Destroy operation. To destroy an existent row, the domain of the row MUST NOT be used by user.

hpnicfDomainCurrentAccessNum.name: hpnicfDomainCurrentAccessNum
hpnicfDomainCurrentAccessNum.description: The current access number of the domain.

hpnicfDomainIdleCutTime.name: hpnicfDomainIdleCutTime
hpnicfDomainIdleCutTime.description: Authentication aging time. If no packet is transmitted during the aging time, the authentication is aged out.

hpnicfDomainSchemeTable.name: hpnicfDomainSchemeTable
hpnicfDomainSchemeTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing schemes of all domains.

hpnicfDomainSchemeEntry.name: hpnicfDomainSchemeEntry
hpnicfDomainSchemeEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing an IP pool of a domain

hpnicfDomainSchemeIndex.name: hpnicfDomainSchemeIndex
hpnicfDomainSchemeIndex.description: The scheme index of domain, which is an identifier of a domain scheme.

hpnicfDomainSchemeMode.name: hpnicfDomainSchemeMode
hpnicfDomainSchemeMode.description: The scheme mode of the domain. Setting hpnicfDomainSchemeMode to none(1) indicates the domain has none scheme. Setting hpnicfDomainSchemeMode to local(2) indicates the domain will use local-server as a scheme. Setting hpnicfDomainSchemeMode to radius(3), tacacs(4) or ldap(5) indicates the domain will use radius, tacacs or ldap scheme. If set hpnicfDomainSchemeMode to radius(3), tacacs(4) or ldap(5), hpnicfDomainAuthSchemeName and hpnicfDomainAcctSchemeName must be set to valid values. And if hpnicfDomainSchemeMode is set to none(1) or local(2), the value of hpnicfDomainAuthSchemeName and hpnicfDomainAcctSchemeName will be ignored.

hpnicfDomainAuthSchemeName.name: hpnicfDomainAuthSchemeName
hpnicfDomainAuthSchemeName.description: The authentication scheme name of domain. If hpnicfDomainSchemeMode is set to radius, tacacs or ldap, the hpnicfDomainAuthSchemeName must be configured with a valid value.

hpnicfDomainAcctSchemeName.name: hpnicfDomainAcctSchemeName
hpnicfDomainAcctSchemeName.description: The accounting scheme name of the domain. If hpnicfDomainSchemeMode is set to radius or tacacs, the hpnicfDomainAcctSchemeName must be configured with a valid value.

hpnicfDomainSchemeRowStatus.name: hpnicfDomainSchemeRowStatus
hpnicfDomainSchemeRowStatus.description: This object is responsible for managing the creation, deletion and modification of rows, which supports active status and createAndGo, destroy operation. To create a new row, hpnicfDomainSchemeMode must be specified. To destroy an existent row, the scheme of the row MUST NOT be used by user.

hpnicfDomainSchemeAAAName.name: hpnicfDomainSchemeAAAName
hpnicfDomainSchemeAAAName.description: The scheme name of the domain, whether the scheme represents accounting, authentication or authorization references the object hpnicfDomainSchemeAAAType. The value of the object must be valid if the value of hpnicfDomainSchemeMode is radius or tacacs, the value of the object will be ignored if the value of hpnicfDomainSchemeMode is none or local. If the domain has no scheme, there will be a null string. If this object is supported, the objects hpnicfDomainAuthSchemeName and hpnicfDomainAcctSchemeName will be ignored.

hpnicfDomainSchemeAccessMode.name: hpnicfDomainSchemeAccessMode
hpnicfDomainSchemeAccessMode.description: The access mode of the domain scheme.

hpnicfDomainIpPoolTable.name: hpnicfDomainIpPoolTable
hpnicfDomainIpPoolTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing IP pools of all domains.

hpnicfDomainIpPoolEntry.name: hpnicfDomainIpPoolEntry
hpnicfDomainIpPoolEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing an IP pool of a domain.

hpnicfDomainIpPoolNum.name: hpnicfDomainIpPoolNum
hpnicfDomainIpPoolNum.description: The number of IP pool, which is an identifier of an IP pool.

hpnicfDomainIpPoolLowIpAddrType.name: hpnicfDomainIpPoolLowIpAddrType
hpnicfDomainIpPoolLowIpAddrType.description: The low IP addresses type (IPv4 or IPv6) of IP pool.

hpnicfDomainIpPoolLowIpAddr.name: hpnicfDomainIpPoolLowIpAddr
hpnicfDomainIpPoolLowIpAddr.description: The low IP address of IP pool.

hpnicfDomainIpPoolLen.name: hpnicfDomainIpPoolLen
hpnicfDomainIpPoolLen.description: The length of IP pool. Default value is 1.

hpnicfDomainIpPoolRowStatus.name: hpnicfDomainIpPoolRowStatus
hpnicfDomainIpPoolRowStatus.description: This object is responsible for managing the creation, deletion and modification of rows, which supports active status and CreateAndGo, Destroy operation. To create a new row, hpnicfDomainIpPoolNum and hpnicfDomainIpPoolLowIpAddr must be specified. To destroy an existent row, the IP pool of this row MUST NOT be used by user.
